se,"web_commit_signoff_required":false,"topics":["closember","code-quality","hacktoberfest","linter","pep8","static-analysis","static-code-analysis"],"visibility":"public","forks":1197,"open_issues":1060,"watchers":5591,"default_branch":"main","permissions":{"admin":false,"maintain":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"body":"### Current problem\r\nI like the idea of the pre-defined styles. What really surprised me, is that you couldn't add multiple styles to a naming-style.\r\n\r\nThis happened when I set `variable-naming-style` to `camelCase, PascalCase` in my .pylintrc and ran pylint:\r\n\r\n```\r\nD:\\>pylint main.py\r\nusage: pylint [options]\r\npylint: error: argument --variable-naming-style: invalid choice: 'camelCase, PascalCase' (choose from 'snake_case', 'camelCase', 'PascalCase', 'UPPER_CASE', 'any')\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Desired solution\r\n\r\nI would like pylint to consider multiple naming conventions for a naming-style. A setup like this:\r\n\r\n.pylintrc:\r\n```config\r\n...\r\nconst-naming-style=camelCase, PascalCase, UPPER_CASE\r\n# or \r\nconst-naming-style=camelCase,\r\n                   PascalCase,\r\n                   UPPER_CASE\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nmain.py:\r\n```py\r\n\"\"\"Example Script\"\"\"\r\n\r\nthisIsFine = 5\r\nThisIsAlsoFine = \"...\"\r\nthis_is_not_fine = True\r\n```\r\n\r\n*Could* output something like this:\r\n```\r\nD:\\>pylint main.py\r\n************* Module main\r\nD:\\main.py:5:0: C0103: Constant name \"this_is_not_fine\" doesn't conform to camelCase, PascalCase, or UPPER_CASE naming style (invalid-name)\r\n\r\n------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nYour code has been rated at 6.67/10 (previous run: 3.33/10, +3.33)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\nBtw. #1013 is about adding the pre-defined styles. This is about being able to set multiple conventions to a naming-style.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pylint-dev/pylint/issues/9735/reactions","total_count":1,"+